com.relayrides.pushy.apns

Enum DeliveryPriority

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<DeliveryPriority>
      • com.relayrides.pushy.apns.DeliveryPriority
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<DeliveryPriority>

    public enum DeliveryPriority
extends Enum<DeliveryPriority>
    An enumeration of delivery priorities for APNs push notifications. Note that this priority affects when the notification may be delivered to the receiving device by the APNs gateway and does not effect when the notification will be sent to the gateway itself.
    Author:
    Jon Chambers
    See Also:
    Local and Push Notification Programming Guide, Provider Communication with Apple Push Notification Service, The Binary Interface and Notification Format

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • IMMEDIATE

        public static final DeliveryPriority IMMEDIATE

        According to Apple's documentation:

        The push message is sent immediately.

        The push notification must trigger an alert, sound, or badge on the device. It is an error to use this priority for a push that contains only the content-available key.

      • CONSERVE_POWER

        public static final DeliveryPriority CONSERVE_POWER

        According to Apple's documentation:

        The push message is sent at a time that conserves power on the device receiving it.
